data.meta_description: Barabbas by Pär Lagerkvist. Par Lagerkvist was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1951. Author Pär Lagerkvist. Barabbas is a man condemned to have no god. "Christos Iesus" is carved on the disk suspended from his neck, but he cannot affirm his faith.
